value.value: The 3rd segment of the male palp, between trochanter and patella.
The 4th segment of the male palp, between femur and tibia.
The 5th segment of the male palp, between patella and tarsus.
A process on the dorsal surface of the male palpal tibia.
A process on the prolateral surface of the male palpal tibia.
A process on the retrolateral surface of the male palpal tibia.
A process on the ventral surface of the male palpal tibia.
The tarsus, 6th and last segment of the male palp connected with the tibia. The name cymbium is mostly used when modified as a spoon-shaped structure containing the copulatory bulb.
The tarsal organ of the male palpal tarsus.

label.value: base of major ampullate gland spigot

value.value: The base of major ampullate gland spigot.
Each of the chemosensory setae on the male palpal tarsus.
Any of the apical setae on the male palpal cymbium.
A process on the retrolateral-basal sector of the cymbium. It may be flexibly articulated through a movable membrane, or a rigid outgrowth.
A process on the dorsal surface of the cymbium.
The membrane connecting the genital bulb to the tarsus.
The basal sclerite of the bulb, connected to the cymbium by the basal hematodocha. It contains the fundus of the spermaphor.
The middle sclerite of the male palp, that contains the spermophore and bears the embolus.
The membrane connecting the tegulum to the subtegulum.

The division of the copulatory bulb distal to the median division, articulated to the tegulum by a terminal hematodocha. It contains the embolus, the sperm outlet, and may also have additional sclerites such as the radix.
The intromittent sclerite of the male copulatory bulb, where the spermophor discharges.
The tube inside the copulatory bulb containing the sperm. It runs from the blind fundus in the subtegulum, to an opening in the embolus. It is often sclerotized and served by many glands.

definition.value: According to Comstock (1910), the spermophor (his receptaculum seminis) consists of three parts: the fundus, the reservoir, and the ejaculatory duct. These parts often do not have clear limits.

value.value: A sclerite of the copulatory bulb arising from the tegulum.
A sclerite of the male palp inserted in the tegulum. It usually guides or fits part of the embolus; may be sclerotized or hyaline.
The membrane connecting the embolic division with the tegulum.

label.value: shaft of major ampullate gland spigot

value.value: The shaft of major ampullate gland spigot.
The base of the piriform gland spigot.
A gland in the paturon of the chelicera, discharging secretion through a small field patch of pores on the fang furrow, opposing the venom outlet.

A file on the ectal side of the paturon, used in conjunction with palpal femoral thorns to produce stridulation. The file is usually made of a series of fine horizontal ridges, but it may be composed of large, well spaced ridges (in Scytodidae) or a scaly surface.
The shaft of piriform gland spigot.

label.value: shaft of aciniform gland spigot of posterior lateral spinneret

value.value: The shaft of an aciniform gland spigot on the posterior lateral spinneret.
The retina of the anterior median eye.
The tapetum of the anterior lateral eye.
The tapetum of the posterior median eye.
The tapetum of the posterior lateral eye.
A gland in the maxilla, discharging secretion through a small field patch of pores, usually on the dorsal side of the endite, sometimes on its mesal surface.

value.value: The base of an aciniform gland spigot of posterior lateral spinneret.

The retrocoxal hymen of leg 1.

A flanking spigot in the triad of araneoid spiders. It extrudes a viscid silk used in the wet adhesive threads.
Tenent seta on ventral or lateral surfaces on appendages.
The socket of the scopular seta.
Each of the barbs with expanded tips on the tenent surface of the scopular seta.
